        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-09T03:21:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in luci-go code base, and I believe elsewhere too, if a function does not need a context, it does not ask for one. Hypothetically, there may be a function that does not have a context and needs to call this one, making a new context would be weird.\n\nL126 in \nhttps://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/770495/1/server/auth/internal/layeredcache/layeredcache.go#126\n\nis an example where I convinced Vadim to remove context because it is simpler.\n\n--\n\ni remember discussions with iannucci where he said that ideally a function declares what it expects from the passed context. e.g. all functions in this file expect db to be there, but you don\u0027t know it until you catch a panic or read implementation. This is a general flaw of context in Golang. But if you don\u0027t have context, you don\u0027t have the flaw :)",
      "parentUuid": "007aa3cc_34f08dad",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 68,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 68,
        "endChar": 61
      },
      "revId": "76af358051a121ba74be3deefb101fd436dbea5c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f237801f_9e080f51",
        "filename": "machine-db/appengine/model/datacenters.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 68,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T01:24:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree it\u0027d be better if we could somehow declare that the context must have a DB pointer in it.\n\nI think that any time you\u0027re calling this method from a call site without a context, you actually should have to create a new context because context is going to be required by the other methods anyway. It doesn\u0027t make sense to call computeChanges without first calling fetch, and fetch requires a context. The fact that this particular method of DatacentersTable happens to not use the context doesn\u0027t imply that you should create and use this struct when no context is available.",
      "parentUuid": "13f53937_589278b7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 68,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 68,
        "endChar": 61
      },
      "revId": "76af358051a121ba74be3deefb101fd436dbea5c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
