      "writtenOn": "2017-12-09T02:54:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure, because the objects could be updated. Suppose:\n.fetch()\n.computeChanges()\n.byName()\n.add()\n.remove()\n.update()\n\nNow what you got from byName() has changed. This is the same problem you mentioned as rationale for changing *config.DatacenterConfig to be a value instead of a pointer.\n\nWe could do map[string]Datacenter here, but then it\u0027s just copying a bunch of unnecessary stuff for each Datacenter when we only use the int64 from this. How about we keep it this way as long as it suffices?",
